{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778273171,"nonce":"P2rM6Xu76uFT0eV/4k68xmKXvWo=","message":"**Demoted; framing superseded.** This issue was filed under the (now-superseded) framing that the Kalman estimator on delayed measurements was the load-bearing gap to C\u0026S Fig 1e Δv. The recipe-bug audit at `/tmp/flavor_ab_review/findings/cs_alignment_audit.md` found instead that the analytical-Δv ceiling at +2.12% was caused by **five recipe-level bugs in the C\u0026S-faithful builder**, not by the absence of an estimator/output-feedback structure:\n\n1. `_apply_delay_augmentation` zero-padded Q on the lag block (vs distributed per `AugRobustControl.m`).\n2. Lag chain tracked observation channel (n_obs=4) not the full physical state (n=8).\n3. `cs_eq15_cost_schedule` zero-padded entries 6,7 (integrators) and ramped all eight entries (vs constant 1 on entries 4-7 + ramp on 0-3).\n4. Ramp denominator + uncapped `(t/N)^6` instead of MATLAB's `min(1, (i/(time/delta))^6)`.\n5. Default `tau=0.06` vs C\u0026S's `tau=0.066` (`minmaxfc_pointMass.m` line 23).\n\nAfter fixing all five (commits `215a06a`, `02cfdf7`, `e1cd78e` on `feature/cs-faithful-8state-delay`), the canonical 15 cm reach Δv reaches **+8.31% at γ_des → γ\\*** and +7.49% at γ_des = 1.05γ\\*, matching the MATLAB-faithful Python port (`/tmp/flavor_ab_review/cs_alignment/cs_matlab_port.py`, +8.24%) within ~0.1pp and Fig 1e measurement (~+7.76%).\n\nKalman / output-feedback Riccati is real (C\u0026S's full simulation pipeline does use a Kalman estimator on delayed noisy measurements with sensory + motor noise) but **isn't required for the analytical Fig 1e replication**. The deterministic Riccati pipeline reproduces +Δv directly once the recipe is faithful. **Demoted to future investigation, kept open** as a tracking issue if/when we want to faithfully reproduce C\u0026S's full noisy simulation pipeline (vs. just their Riccati controller). See updated synthesis at `results/flavor_a_vs_b/synthesis.md` §4.2-revised on `feature/synthesis-cs-target-reframe`.","files":null}]}